  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "As of now, Facebook Messenger does not natively support formatting text with **bold** or _underline_ using special characters like asterisks (*) or underscores (_) directly in the chat. However, there are some workarounds you can use to achieve similar effects:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Copy and Paste Preformatted Text**\nYou can create **bold** or _underline_ text using a third-party tool or text generator website and then copy and paste it into Facebook Messenger. There are many online tools like [LingoJam Bold Text Generator](https://lingojam.com/BoldTextGenerator) or [YayText](https://yaytext.com/) that can help you create styled text.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Use Unicode Characters**\nSome Unicode characters can mimic bold or underlined text. For example:\n- **Bold Text**: Use \"\ud835\udc01\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc1d \ud835\udc13\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc31\ud835\udc2d\" (generated using Unicode characters).\n- _Underline Text_: Use \"_\u0332U\u0332n\u0332d\u0332e\u0332r\u0332l\u0332i\u0332n\u0332e\u0332 \u0332T\u0332e\u0332x\u0332t\u0332_\" (combining underlines with regular text).\n\nAgain, you can use online tools to generate these styles and copy-paste them into Messenger.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Use Messenger's Built-in Formatting Options**\nFacebook Messenger has limited built-in formatting options:\n- **Bold**: Place text between asterisks (`*bold*`).\n- _Italics_: Place text between underscores (`_italics_`).\n- `Monospace`:Place text between backticks (`` `monospace` ``).\n  \nUnfortunately, Messenger does not support underlining text natively.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Use Emojis or Symbols**\nWhile not exact, you can use emojis or symbols creatively to emphasize text:\n- **Bold Effect**: Use larger or capital letters for emphasis.\n- _Underline Effect_: Use a series of underscores or dashes below your text.\n\nExample:\n```\nHELLO\n______\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. Send a Screenshot**\nIf you need precise formatting, you can create a screenshot of your formatted text (using a word processor or design tool) and send it as an image in Messenger.\n\n---\n\nWhile Facebook Messenger currently has limited text formatting options, using these workarounds can help you achieve some level of customization.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
